column3: str

<UIForeground>F201FC</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201FD</UIGlow> Quest Sync<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground>
Despite appearances, Alkmene has a lot on her mind.
Survey flower beds and obtain aetherial masses.
Speak with Alkmene.
Awww! Awen't you just <Emphasis>adowable</Emphasis>? Yes, yes you are!
What will you say?
Hewwo!
Can I help you?
Hee hee! That's what I love about familiars─so whimsical! I have a task that is perfectly suited to one such as yourself.
Hee hee! My apologies, dear─your whimsically diminutive stature misled me. Fortunately, I have a task perfectly suited to an oh-so-grown-up familiar such as yourself.
I would like you to inspect the flower beds north of here. I suspect they will have accumulated some aetherial masses.
Should you find any, please bring them to me. Do look carefully, now─if I needed someone to wander off with the task half-finished, I would have asked one of the other researchers.
Even if you see no aetherial masses at first glance, you must scrutinize the flower beds to make sure. I'm certain you can do it!
Though you examine the flower bed closely, there are no aetherial masses to be found.
An aetherial mass floats over the flower bed, ripe for the picking. Probably.
Did you scrutinize every corner of the beds?
As I suspected─masses of earthen aspect.
The gardens of the Twelve Wonders reflect the balance of dynamic and stagnant aether of all six aspects. An excess of activity in a single aspect leads to this type of agglomeration.
'Tis these flowers' way of bearing fruit, so to speak.
Beautiful as that may sound, aetherial masses indicate that we must adjust the aetherial balance in Elpis to maintain an ideal environment.
There's naught for you to worry your dear little head about, of course. Such magic is as simple as breathing for us. Run along, now!
